   138ŌåÆ### mitt
   140ŌåÆMitt: Tiny (~200b) functional event emitter / pubsub.
   141ŌåÆ
   142ŌåÆReturns **Mitt** 
   143ŌåÆ
   144ŌåÆ### all
   146ŌåÆA Map of event names to registered handler functions.
   147ŌåÆ
   148ŌåÆ### on
   150ŌåÆRegister an event handler for the given type.
   151ŌåÆ
   152ŌåÆ#### Parameters
   154ŌåÆ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to listen for, or `'*'` for all events
   155ŌåÆ-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** Function to call in response to given event
   156ŌåÆ
   157ŌåÆ### off
   159ŌåÆRemove an event handler for the given type.
   160ŌåÆIf `handler` is omitted, all handlers of the given type are removed.
   161ŌåÆ
   162ŌåÆ#### Parameters
   164ŌåÆ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to unregister `handler` from, or `'*'`
   165ŌåÆ-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)?** Handler function to remove
   166ŌåÆ
   167ŌåÆ### emit
   169ŌåÆInvoke all handlers for the given type.
   170ŌåÆIf present, `'*'` handlers are invoked after type-matched handlers.
   171ŌåÆ
   172ŌåÆNote: Manually firing '\*' handlers is not supported.
   173ŌåÆ
   174ŌåÆ#### Parameters
   176ŌåÆ-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** The event type to invoke
   177ŌåÆ-   `evt` **Any?** Any value (object is recommended and powerful), passed to each handler
   178ŌåÆ
   179ŌåÆ## Contribute
   181ŌåÆFirst off, thanks for taking the time to contribute!
   182ŌåÆNow, take a moment to be sure your contributions make sense to everyone else.
   183ŌåÆ
   184ŌåÆ### Reporting Issues
   186ŌåÆFound a problem? Want a new feature? First of all see if your issue or idea has [already been reported](../../issues).
   187ŌåÆIf don't, just open a [new clear and descriptive issue](../../issues/new).
   188ŌåÆ
   189ŌåÆ### Submitting pull requests
   191ŌåÆPull requests are the greatest contributions, so be sure they are focused in scope, and do avoid unrelated commits.
   192ŌåÆ
   193ŌåÆ-   Fork it!
   194ŌåÆ-   Clone your fork: `git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/mitt`
   195ŌåÆ-   Navigate to the newly cloned directory: `cd mitt`
   196ŌåÆ-   Create a new branch for the new feature: `git checkout -b my-new-feature`
   197ŌåÆ-   Install the tools necessary for development: `npm install`
   198ŌåÆ-   Make your changes.
   199ŌåÆ-   Commit your changes: `git commit -am 'Add some feature'`
   200ŌåÆ-   Push to the branch: `git push origin my-new-feature`
   201ŌåÆ-   Submit a pull request with full remarks documenting your changes.
